<div class="container my-5 py-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
            <div class="card fintech-card border-0 p-5 shadow-sm">
                <h1 class="fw-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-4">Last Updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString() %>
                </p>
                <hr class="mb-5 opacity-25">

                <div class="text-muted" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                    <h5 class="fw-bold text-dark mt-4">1. Information We Collect</h5>
                    <p>We securely collect the minimal personal information necessary to provide eWallet services,
                        including your name, email address, phone number, and transaction history. For security logs, we
                        passively collect IP addresses during login and transfers.</p>

                    <h5 class="fw-bold text-dark mt-4">2. How We Use Your Data</h5>
                    <p>Your data is exclusively used to facilitate transactions, maintain account security, and comply
                        with Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations. We do not sell your personal data to third-party
                        marketers.</p>

                    <h5 class="fw-bold text-dark mt-4">3. Data Encryption</h5>
                    <p>All sensitive information, including passwords and transaction PINs, are cryptographically hashed
                        using standard `bcrypt` algorithms. Transit data is encrypted via SSL/TLS.</p>

                    <h5 class="fw-bold text-dark mt-4">4. Your Data Rights</h5>
                    <p>You reserve the right to access, rectify, or request the deletion of your account data. For
                        assistance, contact our Data Protection Officer via the Support channel.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="text-center mt-5">
                    <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-outline-primary rounded-pill px-4">Back to Dashboard</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>